Disable upb's UPB_LINKARR_DECLARE registration in extension_registry.c.

zig's lld does not emit `__start_linkarr_*` / `__stop_linkarr_*` encapsulation
symbols, so building protoc from source under the hermetic zig cc toolchain
fails to link. The linkarr array is only consumed by PHP / Ruby extension
pre-registration, which we do not use from bazel-driven Go codegen.

See https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protobuf/issues/21755

--- a/upb/mini_table/extension_registry.c
+++ b/upb/mini_table/extension_registry.c
@@ -89,7 +89,10 @@ failure:
   return status;
 }

-#ifdef UPB_LINKARR_DECLARE
+// Disabled: zig lld does not emit __start_linkarr_*/__stop_linkarr_*
+// encapsulation symbols. The linkarr registration is only used by PHP/Ruby
+// extension pre-registration, not by our bazel-driven Go codegen path.
+#if 0

 UPB_LINKARR_DECLARE(upb_AllExts, const upb_MiniTableExtension);

